 even global empire. In turn, such literature had a profound influence on Spanish ideas of nationhood, most significantly its own. Elegantly conceived and meticulously researched, The Spacious Word will be of enormous interest to historians of Spain, early modern literature, and cartography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aCartography in literature. 0aCartographyzAmericaxHistory. 0aCartographyzLatin AmericaxHistory. 0aCartographyzNew SpainxHistory. 0aCartographyzSpainxHistoryy16th century. 0aCartographyzSpainxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311063538640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226821191423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226821191/original  a978-3-11-063538-6  University of Chicago Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles